[[File:Anich Haller.jpg|thumb|Peter Anich by Philipp Haller, 1759.]]
[[File:Peter Anichs letzte Karte von der Innsbrucker Umgebung von 1766.jpg|thumb|Anich's last work, [[Innsbruck]], 1766.]]
'''Peter Anich''' (1723&ndash;1766) was an Austrian [[cartographer]] and maker of [[mathematical instruments]].<ref name=Chambers>"Anich, Peter" in ''[[Chambers's Encyclopædia]]''. London: [[George Newnes]], 1961, Vol. 1, p. 431.</ref>

His works, particularly the 1772<ref name=Chambers/> published ''Atlas Tyrolensis'', are among the most accurate maps of their time. 

