The [[United Kingdom|British]] [[British Overseas Territory|Overseas Territory]] of [[Gibraltar]] has introduced the [[postcode]] '''GX11 1AA'''.<ref>[http://www.royalgibraltar.post/contact/ RGPO | Contact Us]</ref> This is pending the introduction of a postcode system similar to that [[Postcodes in the United Kingdom|used in the United Kingdom]].<ref>[http://www.upu.int/fileadmin/documentsFiles/activities/addressingUnit/gibEn.pdf Universal Postal Union document on Gibraltar]</ref> This has been under consideration by the [[Government of Gibraltar]] in 2006.<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20061020003717/http://www.gibraltarnewsonline.com/2006/06/30/government-set-to-introduce-post-codes// Government set to introduce post codes]. ''Gibraltar News''. 30 June 2006.</ref> The postcode is not required for local mail.
==Postal districts== The [[Royal Gibraltar Post Office]] has divided the territory into fourteen postal zones known as 'walks' or 'districts', each with a number or letter as well as a name,<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20130630035343/http://www.post.gi/products-and-services/gibraltars-postal-districts/ Gibraltar's Postal Districts]</ref> but these are for internal use and not encountered in addresses. They are separate from the [[Gibraltar Major Residential Areas|Major Residential Areas]], used for [[statistics|statistical]] purposes.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gibraltar.gov.gi/images/stories/PDF/statistics/Census/census_of_gibraltar_2001.pdf|title=Census of Gibraltar 2001|accessdate=2010-05-20|year=2001|publisher=[[Government of Gibraltar]]|location=[[Gibraltar]]}}</ref>
