{{Infobox country telephone plan | country = Montenegro | country_link = Montenegro | continent = Europe | map_image = Location Montenegro Europe.png | map_caption = Location of Montenegro (dark green) | map_size = 200px | map_alt = | country_calling_code = +382 | international_prefix = 00 | trunk_prefix = 0 | regulator = [[Agency of Telecommunications of Montenegro]] | plan_membership = | nsn_length = | dial_plan_type = [[Telephone numbering plan|Open]] | number_format = 0XX XXX XXX | codes_list = }}
This is a list of dialing codes by town in [[Montenegro]].
==History==
Until Montenegro gained independence from [[Serbia and Montenegro]], the nation was accessed through the [[List of country calling codes|international dialing code]] +381. The new dialing code +382 was introduced after independence and the two codes were used in parallel until February 2007, when +382 nominally became the only acceptable code. As of 1 October 2007, +381 is used only for [[Serbia]] and +382 is the only acceptable code for Montenegro.
==Dialing codes== ===Fixed telephony=== Area codes have two digits after the initial '0' trunk prefix, and local numbers have six digits. The trunk prefix is omitted when calling from abroad.
The following code prefixes are used for network groups.<ref name="atm">[http://www.ekip.me/numeracija/dodijeljena.php Montenegro Agency for Electronic Communications and Postal Services – numbering scheme]</ref>
The old codes were used in parallel with the new codes until 1 October 2008:{{citation needed|date=June 2010}}
